, 
<figureCitation id="DAA62A5B62799D0AEFB2F8CEFDCDED76" box="[489,532,1887,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 155" captionStartId="116.[151,250,858,881]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,187,838]" captionTargetId="figure-58@116.[151,1436,159,885]" captionTargetPageId="116" captionText="FIGURE 155. One of three equally parsimonious trees showing the relationships between species in the L. furcatus species group. Character state changes are indicated on each branch by a black bar. Uniquely derived synapomorphies are indicated in bold and with an asterisk." pageId="24" pageNumber="25">155</figureCitation>
